{
  "texts": [
    "Table 4 reports end-to-end retrieval latency (excluding generation) for 250 MultiHop-RAG queries.",
    "While Naive RAG is extremely fast (0.03s/query), adding reranking (RR) increases latency substantially to 0.88s/query due to the cost of scoring and sorting candidate passages with a cross-encoder.",
    "The overhead of question decomposition (QD) is 16.7s/query.",
    "This is primarily due to the additional LLM inference required to generate subqueries.",
    "When combined, the full QD+RR system reaches 18.9s/query, thus slower than the simple naive RAG baseline."
  ]
}